message: Hello! Thank you for contacting Better Deal Insurance. My name is Chris. How can I assist you today?
Finally, I've been waiting for ages to speak to someone. My claim hasn't been processed yet and it's taking too long!
I'm really sorry to hear about the delay in your claim processing. To assist you further, could you please confirm your full name for security?
It's John Smith. Now can you just tell me why my claim is taking so long?
Thank you for completing security, John. I understand your frustration. Let me look into this for you. Could you also provide your date of birth?
It's 10/05/1984. Can you please hurry up and sort this out?
Great, thank you for that. Additionally, could you confirm the first line of your address and postcode?
It's 123 Green Street, AB1 2CD. Just get on with it already!
Thank you for providing that information. One last thing, can you confirm your email address, John?
It's john.smith@email.com. Now, are you going to help me or not?
That's all correct, thank you for completing security. I'll check on your claim status now. One moment, please.
It's been so long, and I still don't have an answer. This is unacceptable!

I completely understand your frustration, John. It looks like there has been a delay in processing. A possible resolution could be escalating this to our claims department for urgent review. Does this work for you?
Fine, just do it quickly. I can't believe how long this has taken.
Thank you for your understanding. I'll escalate this now and ensure it's prioritized. I apologize for any inconvenience caused. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?
No, that's all. You should really work on your customer service, though. Goodbye!
Thank you for your feedback, John. I'm glad that I was able to help in some way. Take care and have a great day! Goodbye!
